# Audit report required (AIGov)

## When this applies

Any change that **materially affects enforcement**, compliance gates, policy interpretation surfaced to users, or **core governance semantics** must ship with **exactly one** new or updated markdown file under `docs/reports/` for that change set (unless the work is strictly non-functional documentation with zero enforcement impact — still prefer a report when in doubt).

## Required sections

The audit report **must** include these level-2 headings (exact strings, on their own lines):

- `## Evaluation gate`
- `## Human approval gate`
- `## Risk assessment`
- `## Rollback plan`

CI gate `scripts/gate_reports.py` enforces a subset of headings across all `docs/reports/*.md`; new reports must satisfy the full list above for human review, not only the automated minimum.

## Scope discipline

- Prefer **one** focused report per change set rather than splitting across many files.
- Do not remove or weaken existing reports solely to satisfy gate scripts.
